foia:ProcessedRequestSection.foia:FootnoteText: Column one should be the same number as the number of pending FOIA requests reported by each component at the end of FY13. The differences in numbers for AF, ARMY, DCMA, DIA, DTIC, DTRA, NAVY, NGB, NORTHCOM, NSA, OSD/JS, PACOM, SOCOM and TRANSCOM are due to better accounting methods which caused some minor discrepancy in starting numbers.
DHA (Defense Health Agency) is the new name for the component previously known as TRICARE Management Activity or more simply TRICARE. For FY14 and future years, the component is known as DHA.

foia:ProcessedAppealSection.foia:FootnoteText: Concerning all tables in Section VI, not all components process administrative appeals. OSD/JS FOIA Appeals Branch processes the following components’ appeals: AFRICOM, CENTCOM, DoDEA, DTIC, EUCOM, JPRA, NGB, NORTHCOM, OSD/JS, PACOM, SOCOM, SOUTHCOM, STRATCOM and TRANSCOM.

Column one should be the same number as the number of pending appeals reported by each component at the end of FY14. The differences in numbers for AF, DIA and NAVY, NRO, NSA are due to better accounting methods which caused some minor discrepancy in starting numbers.
